  "docs": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Draw samples from a Pareto II or Lomax distribution with specified shape."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The Lomax or Pareto II distribution is a shifted Pareto\ndistribution. The classical Pareto distribution can be\nobtained from the Lomax distribution by adding 1 and\nmultiplying by the scale parameter "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "m"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " (see Notes).  The\nsmallest value of the Lomax distribution is zero while for the\nclassical Pareto distribution it is "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "mu"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", where the standard\nPareto distribution has location "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "mu = 1"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ".  Lomax can also\nbe considered as a simplified version of the Generalized\nPareto distribution (available in SciPy), with the scale set\nto one and the location set to zero."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The Pareto distribution must be greater than zero, and is\nunbounded above.  It is also known as the \"80-20 rule\".  In\nthis distribution, 80 percent of the weights are in the lowest\n20 percent of the range, while the other 20 percent fill the\nremaining 80 percent of the range."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "argument_inline": [],
            "content_blocks": [
              {
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "New code should use the "
                  },
                  {
                    "external_url": "https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/generated/numpy.random.Generator.pareto.html",
                    "href": "",
                    "kind": "link",
                    "target": "random.Generator.pareto",
                    "text": "pareto"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "\nmethod of a "
                  },
                  {
                    "external_url": "https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/generated/numpy.random.Generator.html",
                    "href": "",
                    "kind": "link",
                    "target": "random.Generator",
                    "text": "Generator"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " instance instead;\nplease see the "
                  },
                  {
                    "display_text": "random-quick-start",
                    "explicit_title": false,
                    "external_url": "https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/generated/numpy.random-quick-start.html",
                    "href": "",
                    "kind": "role_reference",
