        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The probability density for the Pareto distribution is"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "formulas": [
              "p(x) = \\frac{am^a}{x^{a+1}}"
            ],
            "type": "math_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "where "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is the shape and "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "m"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " the scale."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The Pareto distribution, named after the Italian economist\nVilfredo Pareto, is a power law probability distribution\nuseful in many real world problems.  Outside the field of\neconomics it is generally referred to as the Bradford\ndistribution. Pareto developed the distribution to describe\nthe distribution of wealth in an economy.  It has also found\nuse in insurance, web page access statistics, oil field sizes,\nand many other problems, including the download frequency for\nprojects in Sourceforge "
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "[1]_"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ".  It is one of the so-called\n\"fat-tailed\" distributions."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "1\n\nFrancis Hunt and Paul Johnson, On the Pareto Distribution of\nSourceforge projects.",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "2\n\nPareto, V. (1896). Course of Political Economy. Lausanne.",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "3\n\nReiss, R.D., Thomas, M.(2001), Statistical Analysis of Extreme\nValues, Birkhauser Verlag, Basel, pp 23-30.",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "4\n\nWikipedia, \"Pareto distribution\",\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pareto_distribution",
            "type": "raw_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "References"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Draw samples from the distribution:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a, m = 3., 2.  # shape and mode"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "s = (we.random.pareto(a, 1000) + 1) * m"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Display the histogram of the samples, along with the probability\ndensity function:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "count, bins, _ = plt.hist(s, 100, density=True)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "fit = a*m**a / bins**(a+1)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.plot(bins, max(count)*fit/max(fit), linewidth=2, color='r')"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.show()"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Examples"
      }
    ]
